threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The code is a shell script that downloads and executes files from a remote server. It first tries to change to the /tmp, /dev, /var/tmp, or /usr directory. If it is successful, it removes any existing files named x86_64, mpsl, mips, arm5, arm4, arm6, arm7, m68k, x86, spc, or ppc. It then downloads the files x86_64, mpsl, mips, arm4, arm5, arm6, arm7, m68k, x86, spc, and ppc from the remote server http://139.177.197.168/. It then changes the permissions of the downloaded files to 777 and executes them with the argument $1.
